article.headline: Howard 81, Coppin St. 74
article.story: WASHINGTON -- Eugene Myatt scored 41 points, tying a career high, to lead Howard in an 81-74 win over Coppin State on Monday night. Curtis White added 17 points for the Bison (8-19, 6-7 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference), who snapped a three-game losing skid. Tywain McKee tallied a double-double for the Eagles (11-17, 8-6), scoring 28 points and grabbing 11 rebounds. Mike Buckley added 18 points for Coppin State, which had won four straight coming into this contest. Myatt was 6-for-8 from beyond the arc. Howard, which led by 17 points at the break, won despite being outscored 49-39 in the second half by the Eagles and committing 18 turnovers in the game. The Bison outrebounded the Eagles 38-29, and hit 26 free throws compared to 10 for Coppin State. Howard avenged a 77-69 loss at Coppin State on Jan. 26.
